# Poll Lifecycle State Machine

> **Note:** This diagram shows the full lifecycle as designed in the specification. Phase 1 implements only status tracking via `VotingOracle.set_poll_status()` — automatic transitions, community voting, and dispute resolution are Phase 2.

```mermaid
stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> Active: create_poll()

    Active --> Locked: lock_time reached (automatic)
    Active --> Cancelled: cancel_poll() by admin

    Locked --> Voting: Phase 2 only (initiate_voting)
    Locked --> Cancelled: cancel_poll() by admin

    Voting --> Resolved: Phase 2 (>85% consensus)
    Voting --> AdminReview: Phase 2 (60-85% consensus)
    Voting --> Disputed: Phase 2 (<60% consensus)

    AdminReview --> Resolved: Phase 2 (admin_verify)
    AdminReview --> Disputed: Phase 2 (admin rejects)

    Disputed --> Resolved: Phase 2 (multi-sig resolve)

    Resolved --> Disputed: Phase 2 (initiate_dispute, within 24h)

    Cancelled --> [*]: Emergency withdrawal
    Resolved --> [*]: Claims processed
```

## Phase 1: What Actually Exists

```mermaid
stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> Active: create_poll()
    Active --> Cancelled: cancel_poll() by admin
```

**Phase 1 Implementation:**
- `PollStatus` enum has all states (Active, Locked, Voting, AdminReview, Disputed, Resolved, Cancelled)
- `VotingOracle.set_poll_status()` lets admin set any status manually
- No automatic transitions, no community voting, no consensus thresholds

## Status Transition Rules (Full Specification)

| From | To | Trigger | Authority |
|------|-----|---------|-----------|
| Active | Locked | `lock_time` reached | Automatic (by timestamp) |
| Active | Cancelled | `cancel_poll()` | Admin |
| Locked | Voting | `initiate_voting()` | Admin |
| Locked | Cancelled | `cancel_poll()` | Admin |
| Voting | Resolved | `>85%` consensus | Automatic |
| Voting | AdminReview | `60-85%` consensus | Automatic |
| Voting | Disputed | `<60%` consensus | Automatic |
| AdminReview | Resolved | `admin_verify()` | Admin |
| AdminReview | Disputed | admin rejects | Admin |
| Disputed | Resolved | `multi_sig_resolve()` | 3 Admins |
| Resolved | Disputed | `initiate_dispute()` | Any user |
